<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3537] getPackage() on Class Always Returns Null</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3537</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Calling getPackage() on a Class object for a Groovy class always returns null. It should return the package object.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Guillaume: &quot; I think it&apos;s probably because we&apos;ve forgotten about it &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; &quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue was originally reported by Vaibhav Puranik in the following thread:  &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Re:--groovy-user--getPackage-returns-null-td23537154.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Re:--groovy-user--getPackage-returns-null-td23537154.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
