                            <comment id="14467080" author="roshandawrani" created="Tue, 26 May 2009 15:15:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I want to use the attached patch for groovy defined classes and have it reviewed first.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After the patch, it works as below:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; testpkg

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Test {}

println &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt;.class &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// prints java.lang.Package 
&lt;/span&gt;println &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// prints &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; testpkg&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is it ok to apply this patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466979" author="blackdrag" created="Tue, 26 May 2009 15:57:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;a test case is missing&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467040" author="roshandawrani" created="Tue, 26 May 2009 22:49:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Jochen, I am attaching v2 of patch that has the test case. Please let me know if it looks ok now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466941" author="roshandawrani" created="Wed, 27 May 2009 01:25:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just noticed that there is a typo in the 2nd testcase I provided in tht patch, so that is wasted. 1st testcase is fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will correct the 2nd testcase later in the day and re-attach the patch. Sorry.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467050" author="roshandawrani" created="Wed, 27 May 2009 02:55:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am attaching the patch that I finally want to get reviewed. I have corrected the test cases and the patch is based on 1.7.x code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467089" author="blackdrag" created="Wed, 27 May 2009 06:21:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;well, I guess it is ok now. Frankly I don&apos;t really know if that is the right thing to do, but I assume we can go with this&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467011" author="roshandawrani" created="Wed, 27 May 2009 06:29:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What is it that you don&apos;t know whether is right to do? I am curious.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467100" author="blackdrag" created="Wed, 27 May 2009 07:10:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;define package has so many parameters that I wonder if it is right to set them all to null&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467052" author="roshandawrani" created="Wed, 27 May 2009 07:20:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, just that ! I thought you were seeing some major issue in the approach.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Those parameters can be used easily later if/when the need arises and most are just pieces of information like specification vendor / version, implmentation vendor / version, etc - nothing that will create any technical issue as such.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would have been nice to see package&apos;s toString() giving back &quot;package a.b, Groovy Platform Specification, version 1.6&quot;, etc but we can set that information later also, if needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will go ahead with the patch then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467088" author="roshandawrani" created="Wed, 27 May 2009 07:25:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;java.net.URLClassLoader defines the packages with all those values as null, so, I guess, there is nothing much to worry about there. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And then, if any values appeal to Groovy for more decoration, they can easily be set later.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467126" author="roshandawrani" created="Wed, 27 May 2009 13:02:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied the patch. Fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
